gomodel:SYNGO_3853  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Stimulation of Pyk2 binding to PSD-95 and Pyk2 autophosphorylation in intact neurons\"\n\nFig.3: \"Ca2+/calmodulin stimulates PSD-95 binding to Pyk2\"\n\nFig.4: \"Stimulation-induced synaptic clustering of Pyk2 in hippocampal neurons\"\n\nFig.5: \"NMDA-induced Pyk2-GFP clustering occurs postsynaptically and independently of Pyk2 kinase activity\"\n\nFig.6: \"Overexpression of the PSD-95 SH3 domain inhibits NMDA-induced Pyk2 clustering and Pyk2 autophosphorylation\"\n\n[Fig.7: \"Interfering with the PSD-95-Pyk2 interaction prevents induction of LTP\"]. Experimental description: - \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared as described previously (Lim et al., 2003; Chen et al., 2008). Briefly, hippocampi from embryonic day 18 Harlan Sprague Dawley rats ...\"\n- Species of the overexpressed Ptk2B, FAK2, Pyk2 is rat (derived from blast analysis of primer sequences CATCATGGATCC-CGCTTTACGGAGCTTGTGTGCAGTCTC and GAGGAATTC-TCACCTGTCCAAGTTGGCTGTAGGCTGGAT)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3853" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
